This paper discusses Information Assurance (IA) infrastructure and how to mitigate risks associated with attacks, specifically phishing techniques. The paper focuses on the human element of IA and how training can be improved to reduce risk. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

The paper also discusses the importance of engaging and memorable training programs, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). 

Additionally, the paper discusses the social engineering aspect of attacks, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). 

The paper also discusses the use of technical controls to mitigate risk, which falls under the category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY). 

Finally, the paper discusses the use of emerging attack vectors, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
